                        <h2> HOW TO AVIOD IT</h2>
                        <p> style=To avoid fog, especially on car windows, you need to reduce moisture and balance air temperatures, using your car's defroster (AC + fresh air), cracking windows, and keeping glass clean; for other items like glasses or goggles, creating a barrier with soap, anti-fog sprays, or proper fit works best. For "brain fog," focus on sleep, diet, exercise, and stress management. </p>
